.:: Puzzle 3x4-Level-2-5::.
4 different games are played: bridge, backgammon, domino, monopoly
There are 4 different nationalities: canadian, argentine, pakistani, italian
The people prefer 4 different types of sport: basketball, cricket, golf, handball
1. the person who's sport is handball is between the person playing bridge and the person playing backgammon##2
2. the person who's sport is handball is the person playing monopoly##1
3. the pakistani is on the far right##1
4. the person playing backgammon is on the left of the person playing domino##1
5. the person who's sport is basketball is on the right of the person who's sport is golf##1
6. the person who's sport is golf is on the right of the argentine##1
7. the person who's sport is handball is between the person who's sport is golf and the canadian##2

.:: Answer ::.
|            |      1      |    2     |      3      |     4      |
| Game   | bridge | monopoly      | backgammon       | domino   |
| Nationality      | canadian   | argentine  | italian | pakistani     |
| Sport      | cricket     | handball | golf        | basketball |

